canonical:
  title: 過營城口號
  author: 偰遜
  language: lzh
  text: 雲深沙路淨無泥碧草如茵散馬蹄五月營城凉似水冥冥山雨杜鵑啼
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 過營城口號
  author: 偰遜
  language: lzh
  text: 雲深沙路淨無泥。碧草如茵散馬蹄。五月營城凉似水。冥冥山雨杜鵑啼。
korean:
  title: 과영성구호
  author: 설손
  language: kor
  text: |-
    구름 깊은 모랫길은 진흙이 없이 깨끗하고
    푸른 풀은 담요 같아 말발굽 미끄러진다
    오월의 영성이 물처럼 시원한데
    아득히 어두운 산비에 두견이 우네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_1200&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Passing Through Yingcheng Gate
  author: Seol Son
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Deep clouds crown the sandy path, pristine without mud,
    Green grass spreads like a blanket where hoofbeats slip and slide.
    In the fifth month, Yingcheng is cool as flowing water—
    In the distant, darkening mountain rain, a cuckoo calls.
  footnotes:
    - Yingcheng (營城) refers to a fortified garrison or military outpost.
    - The cuckoo (杜鵑) is a traditional symbol of melancholy and longing in East Asian poetry.
